1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 17:3384.1, relative to public postsecondary education institutions; to provide
3 for the posting of certain information; to provide information and resources for STI
4 prevention, screening, and treatment; to provide relative to the design and content
5 of the poster; to provide for requirements; to provide for donations; to provide for
6 an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. R.S. 17:3384.1 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 §3384.1. Student health information; awareness signs
10 A.(1) Each public postsecondary education institution shall display signs
11 approved or provided by the Louisiana Department of Health, or its designated
12 nonprofit organization, in the manner provided for in this Subsection.
13 (a) The text of each sign shall read as follows:
14 "Worried about STIs? Just Check!"
15 (b) A website link to the department's sexually transmitted infection
16 (STI) information and resources for education on prevention, screening, and
17 treatment shall be printed on the sign.
18 (2) The department, or its designated nonprofit organization, shall design
19 and produce the signs. Each sign shall incorporate color graphics. Each sign
20 shall be printed on durable signage material that is at least sixteen inches by
21 twenty inches, and the text shall be printed in a large, easily readable font.
22 B. Student health center staff shall display the signs in each patient
23 admission area, patient waiting room, and patient consultation room.
24 C. This Subsection does not require the Louisiana Department of Health
25 to spend its funds to purchase such signs. The Louisiana Department of Health
